title: Pilot
plot: A mobster passes out at a family barbecue and seeks therapy to understand why.

title: 46 Long
plot: As Junior eyes revenge for a hijacking, Tony scrambles to recover a stolen teacher's car, calm Livia after a kitchen fire, and steer Christopher's reckless truck-theft scheme before blood is spilled.

title: Denial, Anger, Acceptance
plot: Tony brokers a bruising Hasidic divorce, copes with Jackie's worsening cancer, and tries to keep Meadow's amphetamine-charged SAT prep quiet--while Junior sends lethal warnings to Christopher's crew.

title: Meadowlands
plot: With Jackie gone, Tony diverts a mob civil war by crowning Uncle Junior boss, even as Christopher demands vengeance and A.J. learns the weight of his father's reputation.

title: College
plot: On a Maine college tour, Meadow presses Tony about the Mafia while he stalks a protected informant--balancing parental pride with ruthless business; at home, Carmela's confession tests her faith.

title: Pax Soprana
plot: Junior revels in newfound power and squeezes Hesh; Carmela and the capos chafe; medication side-effects drive Tony into fevered dreams--and a risky crush--on Dr. Melfi.

title: Down Neck
plot: After A.J. is caught drinking at school, Tony's 1967 flashbacks reveal his father's mob runs and Livia's chill, as he frets that the Soprano gene--and maybe ADD meds--could warp his son's future.

title: The Legend of Tennessee Moltisanti
plot: Indictments loom, prompting frantic gun-and-cash stashing while Christopher digs up bodies, shoots a baker, and obsesses over finding a heroic "arc" that will etch his name in Mafia history.

title: Boca
plot: Junior's prized oral-sex prowess becomes explosive gossip just as Meadow's soccer coach is unmasked as a predator, pushing Tony to weigh vengeance against the limits of mob-style justice.

title: A Hit Is a Hit
plot: A lucrative Colombian heist bankrolls Adriana's hopeless rock demo while Tony samples suburban golf-club status, discovering that music and friendship both come with rigged scorecards.

title: Nobody Knows Anything
plot: Word that Pussy might be an FBI rat pits loyalty against fear; a bath-house test fails, Detective Makazian dives to his death, and Tony spies the real informer in chatty capo Jimmy Altieri.

title: Isabella
plot: Over-medicated and depressed, Tony hallucinates an idealized Italian muse while Junior's hired gunmen move in--only for Christopher's timely visit to botch the hit and ignite ruthless reprisal.

title: I Dream of Jeannie Cusamano
plot: Tony learns Livia and Junior ordered his murder, unleashes a retaliatory bloodbath, and, as indictments rain down, raises a glass to "the little moments" with family amid a thunderstorm.

title: Guy Walks Into a Psychiatrist's Office
plot: Pussy returns after months in hiding, Chris starts a boiler room stock operation, and Tony's long-lost sister shows up on the doorstep.

title: Do Not Resuscitate
plot: Junior leaves prison due to ill health and placed under house arrest, while Livia's health also declines. Pussy begins talking with someone interested in learning more about Tony.

title: Toodle-Fucking-Oo
plot: Richie Aprile gets out after ten years in prison and starts reasserting his authority while unaware of the changes made in the crime family's archetype. Meadow gets in trouble after a party gets out of hand.

title: Commendatori
plot: Tony, Paulie and Chris travel to Naples to conduct a business deal, while Pussy becomes more stressed over trying to balance his secret lives.

title: Big Girls Don't Cry
plot: Paulie and Silvio get promoted, Furio gets welcomed, Pussy gets pushed aside, and Chris gets frustrated with his Hollywood aspirations while Janice and Richie become romantically involved much to Tony's disapproval.

title: The Happy Wanderer
plot: Tony's old school friend digs himself into trouble with his gambling, while Tony's family problems only continue to grow.

title: D-Girl
plot: Anthony continues to cause problems at home, while Pussy's divided loyalties cause him greater anguish.

title: Full Leather Jacket
plot: Rebellion by some of the lower soldiers ends in bloodshed, while Carmela starts intimidating her neighbors to help Meadow's chances at Georgetown.

title: From Where to Eternity
plot: Chris awakens from his coma with a message from the afterlife for Tony and Paulie. Carmela, meanwhile, wants Tony to get a "cut", specifically a vasectomy.

title: Bust-Out
plot: Tony continues putting the squeeze on David, while Richie discusses the possibility with Junior of removing some competition while 'Big Pussy' Bonpensiero continues to be an informant.

title: House Arrest
plot: Junior feels the restrictions of his house arrest acutely, while Tony starts putting in hours at his actual job to allay FBI suspicions, while Junior and Richie uses the garbage pick up routes for a double purpose.

title: The Knight in White Satin Armor
plot: Richie and Janice get engaged, but Richie's violent temper reaches a fever pitch. Tony, meanwhile, breaks up with Irina, much to her dismay.

title: Funhouse
plot: Tony gets sick from food poisoning and blames Artie's restaurant. Pussy, meanwhile, reaches the end of the line.

title: Mr. Ruggerio's Neighborhood
plot: The FBI has trouble finding a new informant, so they attempt to bug the Soprano home.

title: Proshai, Livushka
plot: An unexpected death brings the whole family together one more time, and old tensions resurface while at the funeral.

title: Fortunate Son
plot: Chris becomes a made man, while Tony experiences another panic attack. Meadow continues to seethe over Tony's treatment of her boyfriend.

title: Employee of the Month
plot: Dr. Melfi has a personal crisis. Janice has a dispute with Svetlana. Ralphie gets passed over for a promotion and Jackie Jr. gets involved in the family's crime activities.

title: Another Toothpick
plot: Tony and Carmela try a therapy session together and ends it angrily. Artie, meanwhile, tries to move in on Adriana. Bobby 'Bacala' Sr. comes out of retirement for one last job much to his son's objection after it ends tragically.

title: University
plot: Noah's and Meadow's relationship is disrupted by her roommate, while Ralphie starts getting rough with one of the strippers from the Bada Bing causing Tony to intervene and questionably violating one of the mafia codes of conduct.

title: Second Opinion
plot: Junior continues his cancer treatments, but the prognosis is iffy. Chris, meanwhile, finds himself under suspicion from Paulie.

title: He Is Risen
plot: Tensions rise between Tony and Ralphie until circumstances demand that they resolve their differences. Meadow gets involved with Jackie's son, and ends up in trouble.

title: The Telltale Moozadell
plot: Tony continues seeing Gloria, another of Dr. Melfi's patients, while Meadow continues seeing Jackie Jr.

title: To Save Us All from Satan's Power
plot: Tony starts having flashbacks about Pussy's betrayal, and then later discovers that Jackie Jr. has been failing in his responsibilities.

title: Pine Barrens
plot: While Silvio has the flu, Chris and Paulie run his collections for him, which results in the pair getting lost in the woods and nearly freezing to death while Tony's affair with Gloria goes sour as does Meadow's relationship with Jackie Jr.

title: Amour Fou
plot: Gloria grows increasingly demanding until Tony realizes who she is, and Jackie Jr. ends up in very serious trouble when Chris realizes who he is.

title: Army of One
plot: Ralphie issues his final decision on the fate of Jackie Jr., Anthony Jr., faces military school after getting expelled, Paulie and Ralphie have a financial conflict while the FBI assigns Adriana a new "friend."

title: For All Debts Public and Private
plot: Chris puts a ghost from his past to rest, while Carmela grows uneasy about her future.

title: No Show
plot: Chris' success earns him some jealousy, Adriana learns the truth about her friend, and Meadow still claims that Jackie Jr.'s death still weighs heavily on her.

title: Christopher
plot: Columbus Day ignites tensions between Italians and Native Americans, and Bobby receives devastating news about his wife.

title: The Weight
plot: A joke sparks a series of hit contracts, while Carmela finds herself happier than perhaps she should be that Furio will be around for good.

title: Pie-o-My
plot: Ralph buys a racehorse, but Tony ends up more attached to it than Ralphie is. Carmela starts trying to invest in her future.

title: Everybody Hurts
plot: Tony feels depressed over the negative impact he has on people who don't deserve it, while Carmela tries to set up Furio with a friend, AJ is uncomfortable with his girlfriend's wealth, Artie attempts a new business venture.

title: Watching Too Much Television
plot: Adriana learns that life is not like TV shows, while Tony discovers that a former girlfriend has moved on, along with Ralphie and others they scam the Department of Housing and Urban Development.

title: Mergers and Acquisitions
plot: Paulie has to take care of some rough relationships for his mother, while Tony's fancy for a fellow horse fancier lands him in trouble with Carmela.

title: Whoever Did This
plot: Ralph's callous behavior finally steps over the line, while Chris gets deeper into his heroin addiction and Uncle Junior's mental capacity begins to become in question.

title: The Strong, Silent Type
plot: In the midst of suspicions that he killed Ralph, Tony tries to intervene to get Chris clean and sober.

title: Calling All Cars
plot: Tony's dreams seem to tell him where his life is headed, but he still feels as though he's out of control.

title: Eloise
plot: Carmela and Furio grow too close for safety, while Paulie discovers that he's not as big a fish as he thought he was.

title: Whitecaps
plot: Junior's trial comes to an end, but Tony's trials are just getting underway. Also, the Sopranos almost purchase a house on the beach.

title: Two Tonys
plot: Some of the old guards are released from prison and want to get back in the action. Chris and Paulie are at each other's throats over matters of money and respect, and Tony decides to tell Dr. Melfi what's really on his mind.

title: Rat Pack
plot: A passing makes way for fresh wounds, while cousin Tony wants to put his past behind him. Tony Soprano, meanwhile, discovers a traitor.

title: Where's Johnny?
plot: With Carmine's passing and Feech's arrival, turf wars are breaking out around New Jersey. Junior's mental health, meanwhile, starts to decline.

title: All Happy Families
plot: Feech makes a pain of himself by trying to return to his past glory. Carmela tries to work with Anthony's teacher to rein in their out-of-control son.

title: Irregular Around the Margins
plot: A car crash puts Tony and Adriana in a compromising position, and Cousin Tony tries to keep Chris from getting the wrong impression and the wrong information.

title: Sentimental Education
plot: Carmela has another furtive romance collapse, while Tony B. throws away a chance to turn his life around.

title: In Camelot
plot: Tony learns about his father through the man's mistress, while Chris' friend learns that there are habits more harmful to your health than heroin. Junior becomes obsessed in attending funerals but that leads to a change in his mood.

title: Marco Polo
plot: An uncomfortable party leads Tony and Carmela to a partial reconciliation, while cousin Tony gets an offer he decides not to refuse.

title: Unidentified Black Males
plot: Tony finds out that his cousin wants a bigger share of responsibilities, while Finn makes an embarrassing discovery about Vito.

title: Cold Cuts
plot: Chris and cousin Tony do some digging to make sure old secrets stay buried, while Janice puts her marriage in jeopardy with her fierce temper.

title: The Test Dream
plot: Cousin Tony heads off to avenge the death of his good friend, while a dream reveals to Tony what he must do to prevent a full-scale war.

title: Long Term Parking
plot: Tony makes a request to Johnny Sack on behalf of his cousin, and Adriana confesses to Chris.

title: All Due Respect
plot: Tony realizes that he must take care of family messes himself in order to keep the peace within his own clan.

title: Members Only
plot: Gene Pontecorvo makes a final break from the mob life, while Junior's paranoid delusions could be the end of Tony.

title: Join the Club
plot: The family tries to cope with Tony's hospitalization and deteriorating condition, while Tony begins to hallucinate a new life parallel to his own.

title: Mayham
plot: While the gang begins to turn on itself, Tony finds himself at the threshold, while Christopher gives another try to enter the movie business, however this time as a producer rather than a screenwriter.

title: The Fleshy Part of the Thigh
plot: Tony goes home and returns to business, perhaps with a new frame of mind. Paulie receives a shock about his mother.

title: Mr. & Mrs. John Sacrimoni Request
plot: Johnny Sack is granted permission to attend his daughter's wedding. Tony improves his personal security and Vito's secret double life is exposed.

title: Live Free or Die
plot: Tony hires help from overseas to fulfill a favor he was asked for by Johnny Sack and decides if one of his top earners deserves a second chance as he acknowledges to Dr. Melfi he was given a second chance when he survived his gun shot wound.

title: Luxury Lounge
plot: Christopher and Carmine travel to Hollywood to take the next step in making their movie but quickly realize they're out of their depth. Artie feuds with Benny after his restaurant falls prey to one of Tony's scams.

title: Johnny Cakes
plot: Vito considers starting a new life in New Hampshire, while Anthony Jr. looking for a purpose and finds it when he continues his pursuit of revenge against Junior, and Tony meets an attractive real estate agent.

title: The Ride
plot: Paulie finds public opinion turned against him after an amusement ride accident. Christopher tries to start a new life as a husband and father.

title: Moe n' Joe
plot: Tony reflects on how growing up with Janice colors his attitudes now, while Vito tries to make a new life for himself in New Hampshire.

title: Cold Stones
plot: Phil takes out his revenge, while Tony grows frustrated with Anthony Jr's lack of ambition or work ethic.

title: Kaisha
plot: Tony and Phil begin an explosive conflict that puts Phil in the hospital, while Christopher and Tony both embark on new romances with the same woman.

title: Soprano Home Movies
plot: Carmela and Tony go away to Bobby's cabin upstate New York for Tony's birthday. Meanwhile A.J. is throwing a party at the Soprano home.

title: Stage 5
plot: Johnny Sack finds out he only has 3 months to live. Meanwhile, 'Cleaver' premieres and is a hit, while Carmela has mixed emotions about it, saying too much of it is based on Tony.

title: Remember When
plot: While forced to lay low in Miami, Tony begins to question Paulie's loyalty. Junior and Phil Leotardo both make moves to gain power in their respective territories.

title: Chasing It
plot: Tony hits an unlucky series of gambling losses, causing tension with both Carmela and Hesh. AJ and Blanca decide to make major changes in their relationship.

title: Walk Like a Man
plot: Christopher's father-in-law is the unwitting catalyst of a new feud between Christopher and Paulie. AJ struggles with depression.

title: Kennedy and Heidi
plot: After a tragedy hits the family, Tony gets away from it all when things get too hard to handle.

title: The Second Coming
plot: Tony fails to reason with Phil as more problems increase with Anthony Jr as his depression worsens.

title: The Blue Comet
plot: The allegiance of those closest to Tony is put to the test. A case of mistaken identity has serious ramifications.

title: Made in America
plot: Tony and his family have to stay in hiding until Phil Leotardo is dealt with. His family doesn't like the lifestyle they have been forced to adopt. AJ and Meadow move onto the next step in their lives. Tony confronts Junior one last time.
